				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You could put an indirect JMP at the end of every mainloop.  But then temporary states would be limited to one per vblank (or per loop-around).
<br />
<br />When I've used multiple NMI vectors, I had it point to RAM and placed a JMP absolute instruction there.  It's like a fake vector address, and that is a mere 3 cycles/3 bytes overhead for full control of the NMI (just be sure it can't trigger while you've partially updated the 'vector' address, heh).  Garage Cart #1 and #2 both use a setup like this also, for the many reset and NMI vectors needed.  With IRQs as well, on Squeedo this technique was the fast way to handle the various IRQ sources (but with only one active at a time).</div>

